text: Quenemo is a city in Osage County, Kansas, United States. It is along the Marais des Cygnes River. In 2020, 288 people lived there. ==History== Quenemo was planned out around 1870. Quenemo was the name of a Sac and Fox Indian chief. A fire in 1878 destroyed a lot of the town. Quenemo had a lot of growth in 1884 after the AT&SF; railroad was built through it. ==Geography== Quenemo is at (38.580223, -95.526614). The United States Census Bureau says that the city has a total area of . All of it is land. ==People== Quenemo is part of the Topeka, Kansas Metropolitan Statistical Area. ===2020 census=== The 2020 census says that there were 288 people, 125 households, and 81 families living in Quenomo. Of the households, 72.0% owned their home and 28.0% rented their home. The median age was 46.6 years. Of the people, 93.1% were White, 0.7% were Native American, and 6.3% were two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 0.7% of the people. ===2010 census=== The 2010 census says that there were 388 people, 139 households, and 90 families living in Quenomo. ==Education== Quenemo is a part of USD 456 Marais des Cygnes Valley. The district high school is Marais des Cygnes Valley High School. Their mascot is the Trojans. ==References== ==Other websites== ;City * Quenemo - Directory of Public Officials ;Schools * USD 456, local school district ;Maps * Quenemo City Map , KDOT Category:Cities in Osage County, Kansas
